<section class="about-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-hero__inner">
      <div class="about-hero__text fade-in">
        <p class="about-hero__eyebrow">THE ORIGIN STORY</p>
        <h1 class="about-hero__heading">Meet Antonio.</h1>
        <p class="about-hero__sub">12 years old. Already running a brand. Probably drawing right now.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story__inner">

      <div class="about-story__image fade-in">
        <div class="about-story__frame">
          <img
            src="{{ 'Antonio-originalSketches.png' | asset_url }}"
            alt="Antonio's original sketches"
            loading="lazy"
          >
          <span class="about-story__frame-label">The original doodles. All of them.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-story__content fade-in fade-in--delay">
        <h2 class="about-story__heading">It started with a simple idea.</h2>
        <p>Antonio asked his family to draw just two things: a pair of eyes and a mouth. That was the spark. He took those tiny features and built entire characters around them — bodies, personalities, names, backstories. All from his own imagination.</p>
        <p>Every character you see started that way. A face that someone else sketched, and a whole world that Antonio created around it. Annabelle, Brian, Ethan, Martin, Jim, Ian, Kiran, Steve, Peter, John — he named them all. He wrote their personalities. He decided who they were.</p>
        <p>DoodleType is what happens when a 12-year-old takes a tiny idea and runs with it further than anyone expected.</p>

        <div class="about-story__stats">
          <div class="about-story__stat">
            <span class="about-story__stat-number">10</span>
            <span class="about-story__stat-label">Original Characters</span>
          </div>
          <div class="about-story__stat">
            <span class="about-story__stat-number">12</span>
            <span class="about-story__stat-label">Years Old</span>
          </div>
          <div class="about-story__stat">
            <span class="about-story__stat-number">100%</span>
            <span class="about-story__stat-label">Hand-Drawn</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-values">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="about-values__heading fade-in">What DoodleType stands for</h2>
    <div class="about-values__grid">
      <div class="about-values__item fade-in">
        <span class="about-values__icon">✏️</span>
        <h3>Hand-Drawn Everything</h3>
        <p>Every character is sketched by Antonio himself. No stock art, no generators.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-values__item fade-in">
        <span class="about-values__icon">🖍️</span>
        <h3>Wear Your Weird</h3>
        <p>These characters have personality. Wear the one that matches yours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-values__item fade-in">
        <span class="about-values__icon">💯</span>
        <h3>Real Quality</h3>
        <p>100% cotton. Hand-printed. Built to last longer than a school year.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-cta__inner fade-in">
      <h2>Ready to pick your character?</h2>
      <p>10 weirdos. All hand-drawn. All $29.</p>
      <a href="/collections/all" class="btn btn--primary btn--large">Shop the Collection</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

